Submission and processing of summaries in Germany
Entrepreneurs who make intra-Community deliveries from Germany to other EC member states or take part in triangular transactions must hand over ZM quarterly, in which intra-Community deliveries are listed by acquirer (§ 18a (1) UStG).
The ZM must be delivered no later than the 10th day of the month following the calendar quarter in question.
If a long-term extension is granted for the submission of VAT pre-registrations, this also applies to the Zm.
The ZM must be handed over to the CLO.
Since 1 January 2007, the electronic levy has been compulsory.
The competent FA can allow exemptions for individual tax-resistant measures in order to avoid unfavorable hardships.
If the tax payer finds that the ZM was defective, he is obliged to submit a correction ZM within one month.
In the event of a non-submission of the ZM, the CLO will initiate a coercive procedure.
This includes the following steps: - first reminder - second reminder, linked to the threat of a penalty payment and - fixing the penalty payment.
Although the German tax code allows the imposition of a penalty payment of up to €25,000 (§ 329 AO), the CLO sets a three-stage penalty payment of €125, €250 and €500.
In addition, section 26a (1) No. 5 of the UStG stipulates that the tax payer acts in breach of the law if he intentionally or recklessly fails to deliver a Zm correctly, not completely or in time, or if he does not correct a ZM or does not correct it in time.
This infringement can be punishable by a fine of up to €5,000.
Data on intra-Community deliveries cannot be entered into the MIAS BY THE FÄ, because only the CLO is responsible for the processing of the Zm.
The data of the ZM is stored only with the CLO.
The information from the summary reports is only available to the FÄ after their processing by the CLO.
The deadlines for processing ZM are laid down in Council Regulation (EC) No 1798 / 2003.
ZM data must be stored within three months of the relevant calendar quarter (in MIAS).
In the case of incorrect VAT ID number in the ZM of German tax evaders, the German clo will receive a notification "o _ mctl" from the other Member State.
The CLO then turns to the entrepreneur and asks for the right data.
